						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Amṛitaghaṭēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sundarapāṇḍya.</p>						

						<p>The title of the king and the date have been lost in the beginning of the inscription which is built in.</p>						

						<p>This seems to record some provision made for the excavation of a <hi rend="italic">veḍi</hi> (?) in the temple by the Paradavar of <hi rend="italic">kaḍalvaṭṭam.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
